@startuml
title Geiger Counter IoT Sensor - Deployment Sequence

actor User
participant "ESP8266\n(WEMOS D1 mini Pro)" as ESP8266
participant "Geiger Counter\nModule" as Geiger
participant "WiFi Network" as WiFi
participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTT
participant "Node-RED" as NodeRED
participant "GMC.MAP\nPlatform" as GMCMAP

== System Initialization ==
User -> ESP8266: Power On & Deploy Firmware
activate ESP8266
ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Load settings.h\n(WiFi credentials, MQTT config)
ESP8266 -> Geiger: Initialize GPIO Pin\n(Pulse Detection)
activate Geiger
ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Setup Interrupt Handler\nfor Pulse Counting

== Network Connection ==
ESP8266 -> WiFi: Connect to WiFi Network
activate WiFi
WiFi --> ESP8266: Connection Established
ESP8266 -> MQTT: Connect to MQTT Broker\n(using credentials)
activate MQTT
MQTT --> ESP8266: Connection Acknowledged
ESP8266 -> MQTT: Subscribe to Control Topic\n(for LED commands)

== Runtime Operation ==
loop Continuous Monitoring
    Geiger -> ESP8266: Radiation Pulse Detected\n(Interrupt Triggered)
    ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Increment Pulse Counter

    alt Every Measurement Interval
        ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Calculate CPM\n(Counts Per Minute)
        ESP8266 -> MQTT: Publish CPM Data\n(to data topic)
        MQTT -> NodeRED: Forward CPM Data
        activate NodeRED
        NodeRED -> NodeRED: Process & Transform Data
        NodeRED -> GMCMAP: Send Radiation Data\n(with location)
        activate GMCMAP
        GMCMAP -> GMCMAP: Store & Visualize\non Map
        deactivate GMCMAP
        deactivate NodeRED
    end
end

== Remote Control ==
User -> MQTT: Send LED Control Command\n(via MQTT client)
MQTT -> ESP8266: Forward Command\n(to subscribed topic)
ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Process Command\n(Turn LED On/Off)
ESP8266 --> MQTT: Publish Status Update
MQTT --> User: Command Executed

== System Monitoring ==
User -> GMCMAP: View Radiation Map\n& Historical Data
activate GMCMAP
GMCMAP --> User: Display Sensor Location\n& Radiation Levels
deactivate GMCMAP

deactivate MQTT
deactivate WiFi
deactivate Geiger
deactivate ESP8266

@enduml
